---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout hideNavbar={true}>

  <section class="min-h-screen px-6 py-20">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">

      <h1 
        class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-bold mb-6 text-shadow-purple text-center"
        data-aos="fade-right"
      >
        Building My Portfolio
      </h1>

      <p 
        class="text-lg text-gray-400 mb-12 text-center"
        data-aos="fade-right"
        data-aos-delay="100"
      >
        Not a tutorial — just how I built this and what I figured out along the way.
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-8 text-gray-300 text-lg leading-relaxed">

        <div data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-delay="200">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-2">The Idea</h2>
          <p>I didn't want a basic “here are my projects” page. I wanted something that actually looks cool — simple, smooth, and a bit fun to scroll through.</p>
        </div>

        <div data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-delay="300">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Tech I Used</h2>
          <p>Went with <span class="text-primary font-bold" >Astro</span> because it's fast and just makes sense for a portfolio. <span class="text-primary font-bold">Tailwind</span> made styling easier so I didn't have to fight CSS every 5 minutes.</p>
        </div>

        <div data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-delay="400">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Design</h2>
          <p><span class="text-primary font-bold">Dark theme</span> was obvious. Looked for a dark themed template online and found a good one luckily. The animated stars especially caught my eye. Added some more purple because I like it. Then just kept tweaking spacing, animations, and hover effects until it felt right.</p>
        </div>

        <div data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-delay="500">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-2">What I Learned</h2>
          <p>Not much. But turns out the small stuff matters a lot. Spacing, timing, tiny animations — they're the difference between “okay” and “this feels nice”.</p>
        </div>

        <div data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-delay="600">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Finally</h2>
          <p>This isn't done. I'll probably keep changing things, adding stuff, and reworking parts just like that if college gives time.</p>
        </div>

      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>